./src - source code for the core ORBIT c++ classes with wrappers etc.

./py - place for python modules and wrapper classes for
       the core ORBIT classes

./ext - external modules source code. After compilation they
        should be placed into the ./modules directory.

./modules - place for .so shared libraries that will be used
        under python interpreter pyORBIT

./examples - examples for pyORBIT

./doc - documentation

./conf - configuration information

./bin - place for pyORBIT executable


============SETTING THE ENVIRONMENT VARIABELES=============
User should define:

ORBIT_ROOT - the full path to the directory pyORBIT

MPI_ROOT - MPI library with bin/ and /lib

PYTHON_VERSION   - python version, an example is>export PYTHON_VERSION=2.4

PYTHON_ROOT_LIB  - should specify the name of the python library with a full path.
                   It is usually
		   /usr/lib/python$(PYTHON_VERSION)/config/libpython$(PYTHON_VERSION).a

PYTHON_ROOT_INC  - should specify the location of the python header files.
                   It is usually
		   /usr/include/python$(PYTHON_VERSION)

PYTHONPATH - should be modified to provide access to the ORBIT python modules:
             export PYTHONPATH=${PYTHONPATH}:${ORBIT_ROOT}/py

ORBIT_ARCH - architecture of the system. Right now it is LINUX only.